<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 8:22PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Alamance
County through 930 PM EDT...
At 822 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Elon, or near Burlington, moving east at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Burlington, Graham, Mebane, Elon, Gibsonville, Haw River,
Swepsonville, Alamance, Glen Raven and Lake Mackintosh Marina.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
